<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="525" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,762,1905]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[868,957,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">apicalis</emphasis>
and s 
<emphasis box="[1025,1081,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">pina,</emphasis>
referring to the apical spine of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
